WEBVTT

00:00:28.042 --> 00:00:29.167
Asuna...

00:01:10.792 --> 00:01:13.292
You're late, Kirito.

00:01:14.833 --> 00:01:16.000
You...

00:01:16.208 --> 00:01:19.542
What if I'd caught a cold?

00:01:21.083 --> 00:01:22.667
S-Sugou?

00:01:22.792 --> 00:01:28.542
That was a horrible thing you did, Kirito.
I can still feel the pain.

00:01:28.542 --> 00:01:33.625
Sugou, you're finished...
Turn yourself in and stand trial.

00:01:33.625 --> 00:01:39.042
What's finished? There are plenty
of companies that would want me.

00:01:39.042 --> 00:01:45.750
Yes, once my research is complete, I can
become a true king, the god of this world.

00:01:46.125 --> 00:01:47.292
You...

00:01:47.875 --> 00:01:52.667
But first of all, I'm going
to kill you now, Kirito.

00:01:57.083 --> 00:01:58.750
Hey, stand up.

00:01:59.458 --> 00:02:00.833
Stand up!

00:02:07.708 --> 00:02:13.208
A piece of trash like you daring to...
Daring to get in my way!

00:02:14.292 --> 00:02:20.292
Naturally, the punishment for that is death.
Only death is an acceptable outcome!

00:02:27.250 --> 00:02:32.750
Huh? The vision in my right eye
is blurry... So I missed.

00:02:38.292 --> 00:02:41.500
You piece of scum...
A wretch like you...

00:02:41.750 --> 00:02:46.333
A wretch like you has
no real power whatsoever!

00:02:48.625 --> 00:02:52.458
<i>Sugou, you aren't any different.</i>

00:02:53.250 --> 00:02:55.833
Die, trash!

00:03:06.125 --> 00:03:08.000
A weak weapon...

00:03:08.792 --> 00:03:11.500
It's light, without any reach.

00:03:12.125 --> 00:03:15.083
But it's more than enough to kill you!

00:04:22.667 --> 00:04:25.000
<i>Go on, she's waiting.</i>

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:53.500
Asuna...

00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:56.917
Kirito.

00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:12.708
Yeah. The final...

00:05:13.417 --> 00:05:17.458
The true final battle ended just now.

00:05:18.542 --> 00:05:20.042
It's over...

00:05:22.542 --> 00:05:27.167
I'm sorry. I still can't hear properly.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:31.750
But I understand what you're saying, Kirito.

00:05:32.500 --> 00:05:34.625
It's over, isn't it?

00:05:35.792 --> 00:05:39.750
I finally... I finally got to meet you.

00:05:44.625 --> 00:05:48.542
Hello. My name is Asuna Yuki.

00:05:49.125 --> 00:05:51.375
I'm back, Kirito.

00:05:54.333 --> 00:05:56.750
I'm Kazuto Kirigaya.

00:05:57.458 --> 00:05:59.458
Welcome back, Asuna.

00:06:36.542 --> 00:06:41.958
<i>The feelings I've hidden</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:06:41.958 --> 00:06:47.458
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:06:57.750 --> 00:07:08.042
<i>Seeking only a miracle, I wander</i>
<i>through an endless darkness</i>

00:07:08.167 --> 00:07:18.750
<i>If I stay here, I won't</i>
<i>ever see the future again</i>

00:07:18.833 --> 00:07:24.042
<i>Tonight the moon summons me again.</i>
<i>Though I still cannot speak,</i>

00:07:24.042 --> 00:07:27.833
<i>I keep crying out in my heart</i>

00:07:28.958 --> 00:07:34.250
<i>My hidden feelings</i>
<i>are crying out in pain</i>

00:07:34.458 --> 00:07:39.375
<i>Holding a sure promise in my hand</i>

00:07:39.542 --> 00:07:45.083
<i>If I can stay stronger a bit longer,</i>

00:07:45.083 --> 00:07:51.167
<i>I will go beyond</i>
<i>this sky right in front of me</i>

00:07:52.958 --> 00:07:59.500
<i>I will reach out towards</i>
<i>the future ahead of me</i>

00:08:04.917 --> 00:08:08.917
"The World Seed"

00:08:09.417 --> 00:08:12.167
"Friday, May 16, 2025"

00:08:12.167 --> 00:08:15.333
So this sentence construction--

00:08:16.042 --> 00:08:18.292
That's all for today.

00:08:18.542 --> 00:08:24.583
I'll be sending homework files 25 and 26.
Be sure to upload them by next week.

00:08:44.958 --> 00:08:47.583
Sorry to make you wait, Asuna.

00:08:49.167 --> 00:08:52.375
I'm tired. And hungry...

00:08:52.375 --> 00:08:55.333
You sound like an old man, Kirito.

00:08:55.333 --> 00:09:00.042
Over the past month, I feel
like I've aged five years.

00:09:00.208 --> 00:09:07.417
Also, it isn't Kirito. It's Kazuto. Revealing
character names here is bad manners.

00:09:07.583 --> 00:09:09.667
Right! It slipped out...

00:09:09.667 --> 00:09:13.208
What about me then?
Everyone will know!

00:09:13.208 --> 00:09:16.625
It's because you used your real
name for your character.

00:09:16.625 --> 00:09:23.792
Well, everyone at this school was a victim of
the SAO incident, so I bet my cover's blown too.

00:09:26.667 --> 00:09:27.792
Asuna...

00:09:28.125 --> 00:09:32.333
How are you doing physically?
You're still in rehab, right?

00:09:32.333 --> 00:09:35.958
Yeah. I can finally walk
without crutches.

00:09:36.250 --> 00:09:39.250
But they say I still shouldn't run.

00:09:39.250 --> 00:09:40.417
Oh.

00:09:41.542 --> 00:09:43.667
By the way, Kirito...

00:09:44.417 --> 00:09:49.292
Didn't you realize this place is
totally visible from the cafeteria?

00:09:52.833 --> 00:09:54.583
Seriously...

00:09:55.125 --> 00:09:57.417
That screwup cost you lunch.

00:09:57.417 --> 00:09:59.292
Ah! Sorry...

00:10:03.542 --> 00:10:04.542
Ta-dah.

00:10:10.500 --> 00:10:12.833
By the way, is your father okay?

00:10:12.833 --> 00:10:16.375
Yeah, but for a while,
he was pretty down.

00:10:16.625 --> 00:10:22.792
He resigned as CEO and is semiretired. I think
he wants to relinquish his remaining duties.

00:10:22.958 --> 00:10:26.500
I'm sure he'll find a hobby
soon and cheer up.

00:10:26.667 --> 00:10:28.083
I see...

00:10:30.458 --> 00:10:35.042
<i>That snowy day, Sugou was arrested</i>
<i>in the hospital parking lot.</i>

00:10:36.875 --> 00:10:43.167
<i>Following his arrest, he denied everything,</i>
<i>trying to pin all the blame on Akihiko Kayaba.</i>

00:10:43.333 --> 00:10:49.625
<i>But once one of his staff was brought in for</i>
<i>questioning, he quickly confessed to everything.</i>

00:10:50.167 --> 00:10:56.667
<i>Fortunately, the 300 players who hadn't</i>
<i>escaped SAO had no memory of the experiments.</i>

00:10:56.833 --> 00:11:03.125
<i>No one had neurological or psychiatric problems.</i>
<i>They say everyone can return to normal life.</i>

00:11:03.458 --> 00:11:07.375
"Another Terrifying VRMMO Incident"
<i>However, the virtual MMO genre was dealt a fatal blow.</i>

00:11:07.375 --> 00:11:09.583
"Horrifying Human Experiments"
<i>However, the virtual MMO genre was dealt a fatal blow.</i>

00:11:09.583 --> 00:11:11.125
"Fatal Flaw in the Game System!?
After SAO, Another Horrible Crime Occurs in ALO"
<i>However, the virtual MMO genre was dealt a fatal blow.</i>

00:11:12.625 --> 00:11:16.208
<i>In the end, RCT Progress was dissolved.</i>

00:11:16.208 --> 00:11:19.083
<i>And RCT HQ received a serious setback.</i>

00:11:19.083 --> 00:11:19.875
"Apology Regarding the ALO Incident"

00:11:19.875 --> 00:11:23.542
"Apology Regarding the ALO Incident"
<i>Of course, ALO was forced to shut down.</i>

00:11:23.542 --> 00:11:31.042
<i>And the five or six other VRMMO titles on the</i>
<i>market were said to be doomed for cancellation.</i>

00:11:32.958 --> 00:11:38.167
Hey, come to think of it, what happened
to the commander in the end?

00:11:39.250 --> 00:11:42.000
Kayaba died.

00:11:42.250 --> 00:11:45.000
--They say it was suicide.
--Suicide?

00:11:45.000 --> 00:11:50.667
When the SAO world collapsed, it seems
he performed a high-output scan of his brain.

00:11:50.667 --> 00:11:55.333
Does that mean he copied
his consciousness onto the Internet?

00:11:55.750 --> 00:12:00.750
I heard his chances of success were
less than one in a thousand, but...

00:12:00.750 --> 00:12:05.042
<i>That day, I know I spoke</i>
<i>with his consciousness.</i>

00:12:07.042 --> 00:12:11.708
--What's this?
--The beginning of a world, "the Seed."

00:12:12.792 --> 00:12:15.375
Once it sprouts,
you'll understand what it is.

00:12:15.375 --> 00:12:20.250
What to do then is up to you.
You can delete and forget it.

00:12:20.542 --> 00:12:26.250
However, if you have any feelings
left for that world besides hatred...

00:12:27.875 --> 00:12:29.250
Kirito?

00:12:29.417 --> 00:12:32.833
Hey, Kirito. About today's
meeting with the others...

00:12:32.833 --> 00:12:35.667
Oh... Sorry.
I spaced out.

00:12:35.667 --> 00:12:37.083
Oh you!

00:12:37.083 --> 00:12:42.458
In the game or here, when you relax,
you really are one spaced-out, laid-back guy!

00:12:51.542 --> 00:12:56.417
Come on, Liz... Rika!
Don't be so noisy when you drink.

00:12:56.417 --> 00:13:01.208
But... Look at how
Kirito's all over her.

00:13:01.667 --> 00:13:04.833
They shouldn't act like that at school.

00:13:05.292 --> 00:13:08.417
It's in poor taste to spy on them.

00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:14.750
If I had known, I wouldn't have
agreed to a one-month ceasefire.

00:13:14.750 --> 00:13:17.083
It was your idea!

00:13:17.083 --> 00:13:21.042
Letting those two enjoy their
romance for a month...

00:13:21.042 --> 00:13:23.333
You should have known better.

00:13:27.833 --> 00:13:30.667
Are you going to the meeting today?

00:13:33.125 --> 00:13:34.958
Of course!

00:13:45.458 --> 00:13:49.292
Hey, Sugu. Have you ever met Agil?

00:13:49.292 --> 00:13:54.292
Yeah, we went hunting
twice in ALO. He's really big!

00:13:54.292 --> 00:13:59.250
Just a heads-up... He's that size
in real life too. Prepare yourself.

00:14:03.833 --> 00:14:05.333
"Closed for a Private Party"

00:14:11.167 --> 00:14:14.750
Hey now... Don't tell me we're late.

00:14:15.667 --> 00:14:18.917
The stars should always turn up last.

00:14:18.917 --> 00:14:22.542
So we told you to come a little later.

00:14:22.542 --> 00:14:24.625
All right, come on in!

00:14:25.333 --> 00:14:30.083
All right, everybody...
Let's have a cheer. Ready!

00:14:30.542 --> 00:14:34.833
Kirito, congratulations on beating SAO!

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:39.125
Here.

00:14:39.125 --> 00:14:40.208
Cheers!

00:14:40.500 --> 00:14:42.125
Cheers!

00:14:48.917 --> 00:14:51.917
Bartender, bourbon on the rocks.

00:14:57.583 --> 00:15:01.708
--What? Oolong tea?
--Agil, give me a real one.

00:15:01.708 --> 00:15:06.417
You sure, Klein? Aren't you
going back to work after this?

00:15:08.208 --> 00:15:12.000
Can't pull overtime without alcohol. And...

00:15:14.917 --> 00:15:17.583
--Long time no see.
--Thinker...

00:15:17.583 --> 00:15:21.417
Come to think of it, I hear
that you married Yulier.

00:15:21.417 --> 00:15:24.375
I know it's late, but congratulations.

00:15:24.625 --> 00:15:30.042
Yes, but I'm still fully occupied with
getting used to the real world, though.

00:15:30.208 --> 00:15:32.875
In addition, my business
has finally got on track.

00:15:32.875 --> 00:15:38.208
Congratulations, man! Hey, I've been
reading the new MMO Today.

00:15:38.208 --> 00:15:42.333
Oh, how embarrassing.
There isn't much content yet.

00:15:42.333 --> 00:15:49.000
And with the current state of MMOs,
walkthrough info and news will soon be irrelevant.

00:15:49.000 --> 00:15:53.208
It's like the chaos when
the universe was born.

00:15:53.625 --> 00:15:57.167
Agil, what's been going on with the Seed?

00:15:57.333 --> 00:15:58.792
It's amazing.

00:15:59.083 --> 00:16:04.042
There are around 50 mirror servers
and 100,000 downloads right now.

00:16:04.250 --> 00:16:08.208
And 300 major servers
that actually run it.

00:16:09.292 --> 00:16:11.125
<i>After I saved Asuna,</i>

00:16:11.125 --> 00:16:17.333
<i>I took the world seed Kayaba had given me</i>
<i>to Agil, and I asked him to analyze it.</i>

00:16:18.417 --> 00:16:22.292
<i>I learned that the world seed</i>
<i>was a program package</i>

00:16:22.292 --> 00:16:29.250
<i>that ran a full-dive MMO called</i>
<i>the Seed, developed by Kayaba.</i>

00:16:29.833 --> 00:16:33.833
<i>In essence, anyone with access</i>
<i>to a good enough server</i>

00:16:33.833 --> 00:16:39.167
<i>could download the Seed and</i>
<i>create their own online world.</i>

00:16:39.875 --> 00:16:46.875
<i>I asked Agil to upload it to servers</i>
<i>across the world for anyone to use.</i>

00:16:48.500 --> 00:16:54.458
<i>This revived the dying virtual MMO genre.</i>

00:16:54.833 --> 00:17:01.417
<i>ALfheim Online's data was transferred in full</i>
<i>to a new company and is still running.</i>

00:17:01.833 --> 00:17:06.292
<i>But ALfheim wasn't the only world born.</i>

00:17:06.542 --> 00:17:14.875
<i>Several hundred midsized firms and even private</i>
<i>individuals launched their own virtual game servers.</i>

00:17:15.125 --> 00:17:18.167
<i>Eventually, they all interconnected</i>

00:17:18.333 --> 00:17:25.625
<i>and it's reaching the point where a character</i>
<i>created in one game can be transferred to another.</i>

00:17:27.333 --> 00:17:30.833
Hey, the after-party is going
ahead as planned, right?

00:17:30.833 --> 00:17:33.250
Yeah, at 11 tonight.

00:17:33.458 --> 00:17:36.250
We meet in Yggdrasil City.

00:17:44.750 --> 00:17:48.208
"ALfheim, Cait Sith Territory
Above the Capital City, Freelia"

00:18:14.833 --> 00:18:16.083
"Altitude Limit"

00:18:32.833 --> 00:18:36.458
I was worried you'd go too high up.

00:18:36.458 --> 00:18:39.125
It's almost time, so I came to get you.

00:18:39.292 --> 00:18:41.500
Oh, thanks.

00:18:44.792 --> 00:18:47.375
Hey, Big Bro... Kirito.

00:18:47.625 --> 00:18:54.083
ALO has a new company running it,
and you can use your SAO avatars now.

00:18:54.083 --> 00:18:59.000
So why didn't you go back to your
old avatar like the others did?

00:19:01.167 --> 00:19:05.042
The job of that world's
Kirito has ended.

00:19:07.042 --> 00:19:08.292
I see.

00:19:10.042 --> 00:19:17.500
Then I was the first to meet the Spriggan Kirito
and travel with him to the World Tree.

00:19:20.708 --> 00:19:23.333
Hey, Kirito... Let's dance!

00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:30.333
It's an advanced technique they just developed.
You hover, then move slowly horizontally.

00:19:30.333 --> 00:19:31.708
Huh...

00:19:33.167 --> 00:19:35.792
That's it! You're doing great!

00:20:35.625 --> 00:20:36.708
Leafa?

00:20:40.083 --> 00:20:42.833
I'll be going home now.

00:20:42.833 --> 00:20:44.917
Why?

00:20:46.083 --> 00:20:47.167
Because...

00:20:49.125 --> 00:20:53.708
It's too far away.
Where you... where you all are.

00:20:54.708 --> 00:20:56.917
I can't go that far...

00:20:56.917 --> 00:20:58.292
Sugu...

00:20:59.917 --> 00:21:03.625
That's not true.
You can go anywhere you want!

00:21:26.708 --> 00:21:27.958
It's coming.

00:21:34.458 --> 00:21:37.208
What's with the moon?

00:21:57.333 --> 00:22:00.250
It can't be... It can't be. That's...

00:22:06.208 --> 00:22:10.583
That's right.
That is the floating castle Aincrad.

00:22:11.542 --> 00:22:15.083
But why? What's it doing here?

00:22:16.250 --> 00:22:18.292
I'm going to finish this.

00:22:19.292 --> 00:22:24.500
This time, I'm going to beat
all 100 floors and conquer that castle.

00:22:25.792 --> 00:22:26.833
Leafa...

00:22:27.542 --> 00:22:31.667
My stats were reset,
so I'm a lot weaker now.

00:22:32.375 --> 00:22:34.667
You'll help me, right?

00:22:38.250 --> 00:22:40.125
Yeah, I will.

00:22:40.417 --> 00:22:43.125
I'll go anywhere with you.

00:22:51.125 --> 00:22:54.000
Hey! You're late, Kirito!

00:23:06.000 --> 00:23:09.417
--We're leaving you behind!
--See you there!

00:23:09.417 --> 00:23:11.125
--Come on.
--Hurry.

00:23:12.792 --> 00:23:16.167
Let's go, Kirito... Leafa.

00:23:22.208 --> 00:23:24.875
Come on, Daddy, hurry.

00:23:37.250 --> 00:23:39.375
Okay, let's go!

00:24:02.125 --> 00:24:06.500
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:24:06.792 --> 00:24:12.333
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:24:12.958 --> 00:24:23.500
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:24:23.583 --> 00:24:28.583
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:24:29.000 --> 00:24:33.375
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:24:33.625 --> 00:24:36.000
<i>Out of control</i>

00:24:36.333 --> 00:24:41.583
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:24:41.917 --> 00:24:46.708
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:24:46.917 --> 00:24:53.125
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:24:53.667 --> 00:24:57.292
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:24:57.708 --> 00:25:02.667
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:25:03.042 --> 00:25:08.667
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:25:09.542 --> 00:25:12.000
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:25:12.250 --> 00:25:27.339
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>
